6static int
7klist_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
8{
9 struct klist_options opt;
10 int ret;
11 int optidx = 0;
12 struct getargs args[] = {
13 { "cache", 'c', arg_string, NULL, "credential cache to list", NULL },
14 { NULL, 'f', arg_flag, NULL, "list flags", NULL },
15 { "test", 't', arg_flag, NULL, "test for having tickets", NULL },
16 { NULL, 's', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL },
17 { "tokens", 'T', arg_flag, NULL, "display AFS tokens", NULL },
18 { "v5", '5', arg_flag, NULL, "display v5 credential tokens", NULL },
19 { "all-content", 'A', arg_flag, NULL, "List all caches with their content", NULL },
20 { "list-all", 'l', arg_flag, NULL, "List all caches", NULL },
21 { "json", 0, arg_flag, NULL, "JSON formated output", NULL },
22 { "verbose", 'v', arg_flag, NULL, "Verbose output", NULL },
23 { "version", 0, arg_flag, NULL, "version", NULL },
24 { NULL, 'a', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL },
25 { NULL, 'n', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL },
26 { "hidden", 0, arg_flag, NULL, "Verbose output", NULL },
27 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
28 };
29 int help_flag = 0;
30 opt.cache_string = NULL;
31 opt.flags_flag = 0;
32 opt.test_flag = 0;
33 opt.s_flag = 0;
34 opt.tokens_flag = 0;
35 opt.v5_flag = 1;
36 opt.all_content_flag = 0;
37 opt.list_all_flag = 0;
38 opt.json_flag = 0;
39 opt.verbose_flag = 0;
40 opt.version_flag = 0;
41 opt.a_flag = 0;
42 opt.n_flag = 0;
43 opt.hidden_flag = 0;
44 args[0].value = &opt.cache_string;
45 args[1].value = &opt.flags_flag;
46 args[2].value = &opt.test_flag;
47 args[3].value = &opt.s_flag;
48 args[4].value = &opt.tokens_flag;
49 args[5].value = &opt.v5_flag;
50 args[6].value = &opt.all_content_flag;
51 args[7].value = &opt.list_all_flag;
52 args[8].value = &opt.json_flag;
53 args[9].value = &opt.verbose_flag;
54 args[10].value = &opt.version_flag;
55 args[11].value = &opt.a_flag;
56 args[12].value = &opt.n_flag;
57 args[13].value = &opt.hidden_flag;
58 args[14].value = &help_flag;
59 if(getarg(args, 15, argc, argv, &optidx))
60 goto usage;
61 if(argc - optidx > 0) {
62 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (0).\n\n", argc - optidx);
63 goto usage;
64 }
65 if(help_flag)
66 goto usage;
67 ret = klist(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
68 return ret;
69usage:
70 arg_printusage (args, 15, "klist", "");
71 return 0;
72}

75kgetcred_wrap(int argc, char **argv)

80 struct getargs args[] = {

82 { "cache", 'c', arg_string, NULL, "Credentials cache", "cachename" },
83 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
84 };
85 int help_flag = 0;
86 opt.enctype_string = NULL;
87 opt.cache_string = NULL;
88 args[0].value = &opt.enctype_string;
89 args[1].value = &opt.cache_string;
90 args[2].value = &help_flag;
91 if(getarg(args, 3, argc, argv, &optidx))

96 return ret;
97usage:

99 return 0;

177static int
178copy_cred_cache_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
179{
180 struct copy_cred_cache_options opt;
181 int ret;
182 int optidx = 0;
183 struct getargs args[] = {
184 { "krbtgt-only", 0, arg_flag, NULL, "only copy local krbtgt", NULL },
185 { "service", 0, arg_string, NULL, "limit to this service", "service" },
186 { "enctype", 0, arg_string, NULL, "limit to this enctype", "enctype" },
187 { "flags", 0, arg_string, NULL, "limit to these flags", NULL },
188 { "valid-for", 0, arg_string, NULL, "limit to creds valid for at least this long", "time" },
189 { "fcache-version", 0, arg_integer, NULL, "file cache version to create", NULL },
190 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
191 };
192 int help_flag = 0;
193 opt.krbtgt_only_flag = 0;
194 opt.service_string = NULL;
195 opt.enctype_string = NULL;
196 opt.flags_string = NULL;
197 opt.valid_for_string = NULL;
198 opt.fcache_version_integer = 0;
199 args[0].value = &opt.krbtgt_only_flag;
200 args[1].value = &opt.service_string;
201 args[2].value = &opt.enctype_string;
202 args[3].value = &opt.flags_string;
203 args[4].value = &opt.valid_for_string;
204 args[5].value = &opt.fcache_version_integer;
205 args[6].value = &help_flag;
206 if(getarg(args, 7, argc, argv, &optidx))
207 goto usage;
208 if(argc - optidx > 2) {
209 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (2).\n\n", argc - optidx);
210 goto usage;
211 }
212 if(argc - optidx < 1) {
213 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are less than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
214 goto usage;
215 }
216 if(help_flag)
217 goto usage;
218 ret = copy_cred_cache(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
219 return ret;
220usage:
221 arg_printusage (args, 7, "copy_cred_cache", "");
222 return 0;
223}
224
225static int
226help_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
227{
228 int ret;
229 int optidx = 0;
230 struct getargs args[] = {
231 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
232 };
233 int help_flag = 0;
234 args[0].value = &help_flag;
235 if(getarg(args, 1, argc, argv, &optidx))
236 goto usage;
237 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
238 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
239 goto usage;
240 }
241 if(argc - optidx < 0) {
242 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are less than expected (0).\n\n", argc - optidx);
243 goto usage;
244 }
245 if(help_flag)
246 goto usage;
247 ret = help(NULL, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
248 return ret;
249usage:
250 arg_printusage (args, 1, "help", "[command]");
251 return 0;
252}
